## Section 1 — Infrastructure Overview & Static Design Contract

### Role of This Section

This section defines the **PHYSICAL, LOGICAL, and ARCHITECTURAL** layout of the system. It describes what **EXISTS**, what **DOES NOT EXIST**, where components live, and how data is intended to flow.

This section is **DESCRIPTIVE, not ENFORCING.** Operational authority, safety gating, and failure handling are defined in **Section 2 — Tier-0 Platform Integrity & System Authority.**

> If any conflict exists between this section and Section 2: **→ SECTION 2 WINS.**

---

### 1.0 Core Design Principles (Locked)

**Primary Goals:**

- Integrity > Availability
- Silent failure is unacceptable
- Partial or misleading success is WORSE than a hard stop
- Recovery must be deterministic and auditable
- User data protection is achieved through RAID-Z2 + replicated backups

**Accepted Trade-offs:**

- Primary storage availability now depends on the Proxmox host
- A host-level failure may temporarily remove access to all data
- A data-loss window of up to 24 hours (RPO = 24h) is accepted

**Non-Goals:**

- High availability
- Multi-node clustering
- Continuous replication
- Zero-downtime upgrades
- Autonomous self-healing

This system is intentionally **SIMPLE, SINGLE-NODE, and OPERATOR-LED.**

