## Section 6 — Networking & NFS Data Plane

Networking exists to protect data integrity, not to guarantee availability. Single L2 domain, wired Ethernet only. NFS is the only authorized runtime transport between applications and TrueNAS. NFS does not provide data authority.

Under storage or network failure: blocking behavior is expected; stall rather than corrupt; stop rather than guess. Split-brain prevention is architectural law. All rules unchanged.

