## Section 7 — Backup & Data Protection Contract

Backups are a safety system, not a productivity metric. Backups are permitted only when Tier-0 is VERIFIED. Backup execution is separated from backup authority. `/var/run/backup_inhibit` is the global inhibit. A backup is considered trusted only if taken while Tier-0 was VERIFIED, completed without error, and produced complete and consistent artifacts. Backup trust does not grant restore permission. All rules unchanged.

Refer to the baseline document for full text of Section 7. All authority rules and contracts remain in force.

