## Section 8 — Restore & Recovery Contract

Restore operations are destructive state rewrites. Restores are permitted only when Tier-0 is VERIFIED AND restore authorization has been explicitly granted. Filesystem truth must never be altered to match secondary state. Mixing restore classes without verification is forbidden. Fail-closed behavior is intentional. All rules unchanged.

Refer to the baseline document for full text of Section 8. All authority rules and contracts remain in force.

