## Section 9 — Monitoring & Alerting

Monitoring is a safety authority amplifier, not observational. Monitoring failure is a system failure. If monitoring becomes DEGRADED, UNKNOWN, or SILENT: Tier-0 must be treated as FAILED, backup execution is forbidden, restore permission is denied. Silence must never be interpreted as stability. All rules unchanged.

