## Section 11 — Backup, Verification & Restore Implementation

All scripts implement contracts from Sections 7, 9, 10. Rules: `set -euo pipefail`, abort if `backup_inhibit` exists, fail LOUD on integrity violations.

Scripts:

- `monitor-backups.sh` — Tier-0 evaluator, Debian VM
- `backup-filen-rclone.sh` — rclone upload, Debian VM
- `pbs-write-marker.sh` — PBS Mini PC
- `check-nfs-health.sh` — NFS health, Debian VM
- `check-nvme-health.sh` — NVMe health, Proxmox
- `dump-databases.sh` — DB exports, Debian VM
- `test-restore.sh` — monthly restore verification, manual

Boot inhibit: `tier0-boot-inhibit.service` sets `/var/run/backup_inhibit` at every boot before cron starts. State is UNKNOWN after reboot until `monitor-backups.sh` runs and clears inhibit. This is correct fail-closed behavior.

